john jennings, from the golden school of irish dancing in new york, won the world title in the competition for 17- to 19-year-old boys on thursday night
second place went to another new yorker, neill reagan, of the inish free dance school in miller place, according to official results released by the irish dancing commission
there were 19 teen-agers in the competition from australia, scotland, ireland, england, wales, canada and the united states
