no one was talking either about how much the first couple is paying in rent, but the house was purchased for them by wall management services, a group of about 20 friends of the reagans. the group, whose members were not identified, gave the reagans a three-year lease with an option to buy, mrs. reagan's press secretary, elaine crispen, said earlier this week
mrs. reagan toured the ranch-style house thursday
it has three bedrooms, six baths, guest room, living room, family room, sun room, butler's pantry and three servants' rooms. it is tucked away on a 1\-acre estate in exclusive bel air, 12 miles northwest of downtown los angeles
the reagans' new neighbors will include elizabeth taylor, joan rivers, zsa zsa gabor, mac davis and burt bacharach
