q. you used the term unscrupulous persons who might abuse the process, but _
a. yes. i was using it not in regard to anybody in the current situation, but in the hypothetical situation that if people wanted to get rid of someone in office, all they would have to do is make accusations
q. there has been the more general case that there's a growing trend toward the abuse of the criminal justice system for political ends, such as to the point when even an investigation is launched, this serves some people as an opportunity to begin a drum beat to get others out of office? isn't this what's happening really in your case and how can the system be rectified so that the mere introduction of an investigation or even indictment, anything short of conviction, brings with it the assumption of guilt?
a. well, i think there are some real problems along that line, and i will be happy to address those when this independent counsel matter is totally completed
now, any other questions? mr. archibald
