the drop from february's 5.7 percent rate was credited entirely to a 455,000 decrease in the number of people in the labor force _ those either holding jobs or seeking work _ raising inflationary alarms among some economists
it's just one month, but it indicates that wages are not high enough to coax second earners out of the home any more,'' said roger brinner, an analyst for data resources inc., an economic consulting firm in lexington, mass
