_eastern airlines was ordered to stop training non-union pilots aboard its aircraft by a cargo carrier that was hired to help the company prepare for a possible strike this spring
_cbs inc. offered significantly increased pension benefits to about 11 percent of its employees if they elect to retire within the next four months
_mcdonnell douglas corp. was the pentagon's top research contractor in fiscal 1987, winning awards totaling $1.7 billion, the defense department said
_international business machines corp. led forbes magazine's list of the nation's most valuable companies for a fourth consecutive year
